# Security Policy

## Reporting a vulnerability

Security issues in {{ identity.project_name | markdown_safe }} should be reported privately
to {{ identity.email }} so the maintainer can triage and patch before any
public disclosure.

When reporting, please include:

- A description of the vulnerability and its impact.
- Steps to reproduce, or a proof-of-concept if applicable.
- Whether you intend to disclose publicly, and on what timeline.

The maintainer will acknowledge receipt within 7 days and follow up with
a triage assessment, a planned patch timeline, and any coordination needs.

## Public disclosure

After a fix has shipped, the security advisory and CVE (if assigned) will
be published at {{ identity.repo_url }}/security/advisories. Reporters
who follow responsible-disclosure practice are credited in the advisory.

## Out of scope

The following are considered out of scope for security reports:

- Issues in third-party dependencies that already have public disclosures.
  File an issue with the upstream project instead.
- Theoretical attacks without a concrete exploitation path against this
  project's actual deployment surface.
- Self-inflicted issues (e.g., a user committing their own credentials).

## Supported versions

Security fixes ship to the latest released minor version. Older versions
do not receive backports unless coordinated explicitly with the
maintainer.
